comments: Allen (BKN) establishes a legal position in Grant's (DEN) path during the pick and he does not deliver contact.
Jokic (DEN) establishes a legal position in Harris' (BKN) path during the pick and he does not deliver contact.
Allen (BKN) is moving alongside Harris' (DEN) path and maintains a legal guarding position as he defends the drive to the basket.
Prince (BKN) makes marginal contact with Murray (DEN) at the start of his drive.
Jokic (DEN) maintains a legal guarding position and absorbs the contact initiated by Allen (BKN) during his shot near the rim.
Allen (BKN) and Barton (DEN) engage and disengage with one another during rebounding.
Allen (BKN) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Jokic (DEN) in the post.
Temple (BKN) legally contests Murray's (DEN) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Correctly called 24 second violation.
Jokic (DEN) makes marginal contact to the body of Dinwiddie (BKN) during his shooting motion that does not affect his driving shot attempt.
Jokic (DEN) slightly extends his arm in Dinwiddie (BKN) as they release from the pick.
Allen (BKN) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Jokic's (DEN) driving shot attempt.
Grant (DEN) jumps vertically and maintains a legal vertical position contesting the driving shot attempt by Dinwiddie (BKN).
Dinwiddie (BKN) does not unnaturally extend his arm into Grant's (DEN) arm during his shot attempt.
Jokic (DEN) ends his dribble and does not take more than two steps following his gather.
Prince (BKN) dislodges the ball as Jokic (DEN) makes a pass.
Jokic (DEN) establishes a legal position in Temple's (BKN) path during the pick and he does not deliver contact.
Dinwiddie (BKN) maintains a legal guarding position during Barton's (DEN) jump shot attempt.
Allen (BKN) does not make contact to Barton's (DEN) arm as he is starting his upward shooting motion.
Murray (DEN) commits a take foul on Prince (BKN).
Barton (DEN) commits a take foul on Prince (BKN).
Jokic (DEN) does not establish a legal position in Dinwiddie's (BKN) path and delivers contact that affects his ability to defend.
Dinwiddie (BKN) moves into Murray's (DEN) path and makes body to body contact that affects Murray's SQBR.
Prince (BKN) legally contests Murray's (DEN) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
